	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			One DoT spell cannot be stacked with the same one, until it has run its course. This will be signified by a blue text saying something like, Orc looks better. They can however be stacked with other DoT spells. By level 16 your DoT spells will be doing 400 damage when stacked over a 1 minute period, and in the same time your pet will do about 150 damage and taking hits for you. DoT spells are best used against BIG creatures (make sure you first find out which are resisited by that type of creature from a higher necro or experimentation). This way some warrior types and your skel can take the hits alternately, and you can do 1200 damage through spells, 600 damage through your pet and take down most mobs 5 levels ahead of you. One tip, remember to regen mana and get some +int eq early so you stack a lot of mana later on, otherwise you'll get about 2mins worth of spells and be left mana-less. These DoT's also give you a chance for 1min of mana regen/dark pact whilst you wait for them to wear off.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
